  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_U\n=\n\\frac{c^4}{16\\pi G}R[g]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{QFT}[\\Psi,A_\\mu]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{topo}[A_\\mu]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{info}[\\Phi]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{bio}[\\Xi].\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nA unified Trawinistic action density is constructed by summing distinct physical sectors.\n\nThe gravitational sector is given by the Einstein-Hilbert density:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_{grav}\n=\n\\frac{c^4}{16\\pi G}R[g].\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe quantum field contribution is:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_{QFT}[\\Psi,A_\\mu].\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe topological contribution accounts for winding, helicity, and gauge structure:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_{topo}[A_\\mu].\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe information-field sector is:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_{info}[\\Phi].\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe biological or organized-complexity sector is:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_{bio}[\\Xi].\n\\end{equation}\n\nAdding all components gives:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\mathcal{L}_U\n=\n\\frac{c^4}{16\\pi G}R[g]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{QFT}[\\Psi,A_\\mu]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{topo}[A_\\mu]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{info}[\\Phi]\n+\n\\mathcal{L}_{bio}[\\Xi].\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThis equation defines a layered Lagrangian architecture: gravity, quantum fields, topology, information, and biological organization are treated as coupled sectors of one Trawinistic action density.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
